  <body>

  <h1 class="text-center"><%=image_tag("famgen_logo.png", alt: "Logo", :size => "100x100")%>Our Family Genealogy Website 
  </h1>
    
  <hr>

    <!--<div id="main-container" class="container-fluid">-->
    <div id="main-container" class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div id="sidebar" class="col-xs-3">
          <!-- sidebar content -->
           <p>Login:</p>
          <form role="form">
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="email">Email</label>
              <input type="text" id="email" name="email" class="form-control" />
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="password">Password</label>
              <input type="password" id="password" name="password" class="form-control" />
            </div>

            <input type="submit" value="Login" />
            <input type="button" value="Cancel" />
          </form>

          <hr>
          <p>Forgot Password</p>

          </div>
          <div id="main-content" class="col-xs-9">
            <!--  main content -->
            <h3>Hello Family Member!</h3>
            <h4>Welcome to OUR FAMILY GENEALOGY WEBSITE created exclusively for the extended families (descendants, siblings, ancestors and all other relatives) of <em>Larry Francis Rohr, Gloria Arminda Medina and Paul Webb Erekson.</em> The purpose of this website is to create a shared library of family records and information where family members can collaborate with each other and collectively maintain a more accurate history and genealogy of these persons. This website is for use by any family member; however, an active user account (with password and email) is required to login.</h4>

            <h4>[Note: A user account is available for each member of the family who desires to have one (at no charge). You may continue by entering your user account information inside the login panel on the left, or if you do not already have a user account you can request one along with a starter password from the Administrator by clicking the "Request User Account" button below.]</h4>

            <form role="form">
              <input type="button" value="Request User Account" />
            </form>

            <h3>Change Language (Cambiar idioma)</h3>

            <div class="form-group">
              <div class="col-sm-8">
                <div class="radio">
                  <label class="radio-inline">
                  <input type="radio" name="languageRadios" id="enLanguage" value="english" checked>
                  English
                  </label>
                </div>
                <div class="radio">
                  <label class="radio-inline">
                  <input type="radio" name="languageRadios" id="spLanguage" value="spanish">
                  Espa√±ol
